# Mobile-first & responsive UI

## Default stance

- **Mobile first:** Base styles target the smallest viewport (narrow phone). Add complexity with **`sm:`**, **`md:`**, **`lg:`**, **`xl:`** (Tailwind defaults) — never rely only on `max-*` unless there is a specific exception.
- **Fully responsive:** Layouts must work from ~320px wide up to large desktops — no horizontal scroll for main content, no clipped text or controls at small widths.
- **Touch-friendly:** Interactive targets (buttons, links in toolbars, icon buttons) should be at least **~44×44px** (`min-h-11` / `min-w-11` or `size-11`) where practical; avoid tiny hit areas on mobile.

## Layout & typography

- Prefer **flex/grid** with **`w-full`**, **`max-w-*`**, and **`min-w-0`** on flex children that truncate or scroll so columns don’t overflow.
- Use responsive spacing: **`px-4 sm:px-6`**, **`gap-4 sm:gap-6`**, **`text-base sm:text-lg`** as needed — don’t assume desktop padding on the base layer.
- Long headings/hero text: allow **`leading-tight`**, **`break-words`**, or **`sm:*` size steps** so lines wrap cleanly on narrow screens.

## Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Mobile stack → row on larger screens
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 md:flex-row md:items-center">

// ✅ Readable width on large screens only
<div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-md md:max-w-lg">

// ❌ Desktop-only assumptions without a small-screen base
<div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8">  {/* add grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 */}
```

## `globals.css` & theme

- Responsive rules still use **semantic tokens** from `app/globals.css` (see the shadcn/ui + theme rule) — responsiveness is about **layout and scale**, not new ad-hoc colors.

When adding pages or features, **verify mentally (or in the browser)** at narrow width first, then `md` / `lg`.
